release_note: We ve fixed a bug that would cause our widgets to show with an unwanted padding on devices running iOS 17
Bug fixes and performance improvements.

We have addressed a rare crash in the latest version of our app. This update is focused on ensuring a stable and reliable experience for our users. Thank you for your continued support and please let us know if you experience any issues.

We ve fixed a bug that was preventing the guided journaling templates from loading only the first time the app was launched We solved an issue that was making the app randomly crash on a few rare occasions
Introducing Tangerine s new Lock Screen Widgets for iOS 16. Now you can know how far along you are to completing your goals for the day with just a quick glance to your device.
This update contains some stability fixes and some changes to our translations.
We ve made some performance improvements when editing a journal entry
Performance improvements and bug fixes
We ve fixed a bug that was causing the wrong period of the day to be sometimes listed on the routine view list headers

We have fixed an issue where the count of remaining habits for a given date would not reflect that day s completions We have fixed an issue where undoing a completion on a habit with multiple completions a day would not correctly update the list item for that habit We improved the overall performance of the app

We fixed a bug that was showing an empty journal entry whenever a user attempted to edit an existing entry We fixed a random crash that was occurring to some users when scrolling through the mood tracker dates.

We ve fixed an issue that was it so that habits set to repeat n times a week would not be correctly moved to the Completed tab when completed on a given day. The app is now correctly ordering the habits according to the period and to the order defined in Manage habits The app will now launch with the relevant day period expanded according to the time of the day
We ve fixed a random crash that was occurring to users running Tangerine on iOS 14
We ve fixed a bug introduced in our latest update which would cause the app to crash when creating a new guided journal entry.

Lots of performance improvements! We did a complete overhaul of the app in order to ensure a smooth and snappier experience. We fixed an issue that was causing the app to lag a bit for users with a lot of saved data. The habit list was completely re implemented making it harder to accidentally complete or skip a habit when scrolling. Syncing your data with the cloud should now be way faster than before.

Introducing: Health Habits How about making the most of 2022 by starting running cycling or maybe swimming With our new Apple Health integration you can automatically track your Health Habits. Just choose Health Habit when creating a new habit set your goal and the habit will be automatically marked as completed once your goal is reached. Bug fixes: Fixed a bug that was causing the app to crash for users on iOS versions prior to 14.7

Introducing: Health Habits How about making the most of 2022 by starting running cycling or maybe swimming With our new Apple Health integration you can automatically track your Health Habits. Just choose Health Habit when creating a new habit set your goal and the habit will be automatically marked as completed once your goal is reached. Bug fixes: Fixed a bug that might cause the app to crash for some users who recently wrote a guided journal entry Fixed an issue with the background data sync

Introducing: Health Habits How about making the most of 2022 by starting running cycling or maybe swimming With our new Apple Health integration you can automatically track your Health Habits. Just choose Health Habit when creating a new habit set your goal and the habit will be automatically marked as completed once your goal is reached.
We ve fixed a bug that was causing the app to crash when tapping Invite your friends on iPad devices.
We ve fixed a bug that was preventing habit reminders from being correctly deleted

Introducing Time Sensitive notifications for iOS 15. Always receive your habit reminders on the precise time you scheduled them without worrying about being bothered by other less important notifications when using Focus. Bug fixes: We fixed a crash when that would occur when users attempted to register their daily mood on iOS 15

Introducing Time Sensitive notifications for iOS 15. Always receive your habit reminders on the precise time you scheduled them without worrying about being bothered by other less important notifications when using Focus.
We ve fixed a bug that was causing the app to crash for some users with habits that occurred multiple times per week on non specific days
We ve fixed a bug that was causing Tangerine to crash for our users in Chile due to a daylight saving time change bug.
We ve fixed a bug that was causing Tangerine to sometimes miscalculate the streak count for some habits.
We ve fixed a bug that was sometimes preventing the passcode screen from showing

We fixed a bug that was preventing the number of completions an habit had in a day from being correctly displayed on the large Widget. Users can now have profiles with only a first name. Fixed some random crashes that were occurring on rare occasions.
We fixed a bug that was preventing the app from correctly syncing the mood entries across devices.

We are glad to finally bring an update that has been requested countless times by our users. You can now easily search all your habit notes mood reports and journal entries with our new Premium Search.

We had previously introduced a bug that was forcing the app to always sync the habits completions to the Tangerine servers even when these completions were already synced. This was impacting our quality of service and this update fixes that.
We ve fixed a bug that would on rare occasions cause the app to crash on launch .
The companion Watch App will now display the habits in the same order defined by the user on Manage Habits

This is a minor update that contains some stability fixes that we wanted to get out of the way before our next big feature. We again would like to thank all the users that are constantly sending us feedback and helping us make Tangerine an awesome app. We are now just over one year on the App Store and it s an honour to be a part of this journey with you all specially during these uncertain times. Stay safe!
We fixed bug that was causing the app to crash when adding a new note to an habit.
We have fixed a bug that was causing the app to crash when unarchiving an habit.
We fixed a couple of issues that could cause Tangerine to crash.
We fixed a bug that was causing the app to crash upon deleting a habit.

You know sometimes when your home renovation just doesn t go as planned Well we made a bunch of under the hood changes on our previous version and with that we introduced a bug that would sometimes prevent users from creating new habits. This update fixes that. Sorry for the disruption folks!
You asked and we heard you! This update makes it possible for you to reorder your habits for any period of the day.
Just a small update with a couple of bug fixes: We have fixed a bug where the habit counter might sometimes show the wrong number. We have corrected a couple of typos in our German translations.
We made some improvements to make your habit list smoother and we are also paving the way for more features to come. Stay tuned!
Fixed a bug that was preventing some users from syncing their habits to their Apple Watch app. Happy 2021 everyone! And thanks so much for your continued support :

You asked and we listened! This release includes: Passcode and biometrics FaceID TouchID authentication for our premium users. New feelings that can be tracked Overall performance improvements and bug fixes May 2021 be a better year for everyone!

More bug fixes people! Yeah again bugs related to notifications buuut now everything should be super smooth. Thanks for your patience and feedback! : And if you enjoy Tangerine please consider leaving a review that helps us a lot! Until next time!
Here s another round of bug fixes you should no longer receive push notifications for habits that have been deleted.

In this version we ve made the app more stable and improved again! our syncing feature especially when it comes to habit completions. As always thanks a lot for using Tangerine! We re extremely humbled and excited by all the feedback we ve been getting and we re working hard to make the app better and better every single day. We re just getting started by the way so stay tuned for more :
We had a lot of users asking us how they could change the email they used to register on Tangerine. This update is our answer to that
We fixed a bug that was affecting some of our users where the app would have difficulty synchronising the habit completions across 2 or more devices.
We have fixed a timezone issue that was affecting some of our users. A special thanks for all the users who reported this to us! You all rock!
On to another round of bug fixes! As always we d like to thank all the users that reported these bugs to us.
Ops! We made a silly mistake on our last release that was preventing some users from making habits as completed. Lesson learned: we should practice what we preach! Working late hours doesn t pay off!

Just a couple of improvement fixes: Users will now be notified via Push Notification when we reply to support tickets. We fixed a crash that was happening specifically to iPad users when attempting to edit a journal entry or post a photo.

Hey hey hey ready for some bug fixes Some users pointed out that 2 of our widgets had the wrong text colour for the all completed message on light mode. Ooops it looks like we like dark mode a bit too much. This has been addressed in this release. There was a very specific error that was crashing the app for users in Thailand with their devices set to use the Buddhist calendar. Sorry about that Thailand. We love you! Last but not least we addressed an issue that was making the journal entries time to shift relative to the user timezone whenever the app attempted to sync with the server for users that are signed in. Welp dates and timezones are hard!

Welcome to our biggest update to date! Our goal with Tangerine is for it to be your guide to daily self care so we re adding a standalone journaling feature which is completely integrated to your routine and mood tracker. You can now see everything you write on Tangerine on a timeline and that includes your habit notes and the things you write about your days when you track your mood. You can now also write down your thoughts as they pop up or explore one of our guided journaling templates. We hope you enjoy this update as much as we do! Our small team worked super hard to make this happen! Last but not least: thanks a lot for all the feedback you all have been sending over the past few months! Feedback is vital to help us improve the app. Feel free to reach out to us at hi bitdreams.co at any time! Have fun!

Hey hey! We have a big announcement on this release after almost a couple of months of hard work! Introducing user accounts: create an account to back up your data sync it between multiple devices and save your progress to the cloud! It s now possible to sync your data from your iPhone to your iPad and vice versa. And yes it s completely free. Other than this we ve squashed quite a few bugs improved the app performance and translated it to Japanese! Stay tuned because our team is on fire! We ll be releasing a couple of pretty cool features in the coming weeks : Thanks so much for being a user. We re very humbled by all the kind words and feedback we ve been getting.
